LABEL: 0x26
ENG: While I was wandering around the island...

LABEL: 0xa2
JPN: ガラガラという音とともに、背中に声がかかる。
ENG: A voice called out to me, accompanied by the clattering of wheels on asphalt.

LABEL: 0x15c
JPN: いつものようにスーツケースを引いて。

LABEL: 0x1d8
JPN: 頬を膨らませながら、小走りにやってくる。
ENG: She jogged the last few steps with puffed up cheeks.

LABEL: 0x246
JPN: 「手伝うって言ったのに。来ないじゃない」
ENG: "You said you'd help, but you never showed up!"

LABEL: 0x294
JPN: 「待ってたのに。裏切られた気分だよ」
ENG: "I even waited for you. I'm feeling a little betrayed here."

LABEL: 0x2f4
JPN: そう言えば、鍵を探すのを手伝うとか約束めいたことをしたな。
ENG: Now that she mentioned it, I did promise to help her find those keys, didn't I?

LABEL: 0x33e
ENG: "I was interested, I swear, it's just..."

LABEL: 0x372
JPN: 「考えてみれば、お前がいつもどこにいるか俺は知らないから」
ENG: "I realized that I had no idea where to find you."

LABEL: 0x40c
JPN: 「それでも探そうとかしなかったの」

LABEL: 0x4cc
JPN: 「ほら、こうして会えたんだし。手伝うぞ」
ENG: "Look, I'm here now, aren't I? I'll help you out."

LABEL: 0x5f4
JPN: うきうきと歩きだす鴎。
ENG: Kamome set off with a pep in her step.

LABEL: 0x660
ENG: "Hey, do we have an actual destination?"

LABEL: 0x6e2
JPN: 「だから、どこに探しに行くんだって」

LABEL: 0x7aa
ENG: "That's the million dollar question, isn't it?"

LABEL: 0x7f2
ENG: "Would it kill you to look before you leap!?"

LABEL: 0x89c
ENG: "Let me take a look at the notebook from before."

LABEL: 0x9fa
JPN: 改めて考えてみると、いろいろと疑問が浮かぶ。
ENG: Doubts started to sprout in my mind as I looked over it.

LABEL: 0xabe
JPN: 「なぁ、これ、ほんとに探すのか？」
ENG: "Hey, you're serious about looking for these?"

LABEL: 0xb5a
ENG: "I mean, this was ten years ago, right?"

LABEL: 0xb8a
JPN: 「どこに隠したにしろ、そのままの状態であるとは思えないな」
ENG: "It's kinda hard to imagine those keys being in the same place after all that time."

LABEL: 0xbde
JPN: 誰かに見つけられていたり、知らずに捨てられていたり……
ENG: Someone could have found them or unwittingly thrown them away.

LABEL: 0xc24
JPN: 少なくとも４本ともちゃんと残っているとは思えない。
ENG: At the very least, it seemed unlikely that all four of them were still in their original locations.

LABEL: 0xc76
JPN: 「うーん。その辺はちゃんと考えて隠したと思うよ」
ENG: "Hmmm... I think they hid 'em pretty well."

LABEL: 0xcbc
JPN: 「とはいえ、小さい子供の考えることだろ」
ENG: "We're still talking about a bunch of kids, though."

LABEL: 0xcfe
JPN: 「だいいち、１０年も残ってるような場所なんて俺でも想像つかないぞ」
ENG: "Like, even I'd be hard-pressed to come up with a place to hide something for the next ten years."

LABEL: 0xd6a
JPN: 「それは羽依里に想像力がないからだよ」

LABEL: 0xda6
JPN: 「なぬ。じゃあ、お前は思いつくのか」
ENG: "Uh, what? Pff, then you come up with something."

LABEL: 0xe22
JPN: 「えーと……たとえば、金庫の中とか……」
ENG: "Umm... What about, like, inside a safe?"

LABEL: 0xed6
JPN: 「とにかく、もし無くなってたら、そのときはそのときだよ」
ENG: "In any case, if they're gone, then we'll just have to cross that bridge when we get to it."

LABEL: 0xf74
ENG: "Well, which one should we go after first?"

LABEL: 0xfba
JPN: 「どれがいい？　羽依里が決めていいよ」
ENG: "What do you think? I'll let you decide."

LABEL: 0x10f8
JPN: メモに並んだ４つのヒントを見比べる。
ENG: I compared the four hints in the notebook.

LABEL: 0x1150
JPN: 『かいじん　が　しゅごする　かいていに』
ENG: 'In the companion way amongst the ocean gods.'

LABEL: 0x129e
JPN: 「海の神様が護ってる海底、ってことだよな」
ENG: "Kinda sounds like it's talking about some kind of 'path through the sea,' doesn't it?"

LABEL: 0x12e2
ENG: "A path through the sea... A companion way..."

LABEL: 0x1318
JPN: 「そのまま読むと海の底だけど」
ENG: "That sounds like the bottom of the ocean. Pretty fishy, if you ask me."

LABEL: 0x138c
ENG: "Maybe instead of the sea, it's like a river, or..."

LABEL: 0x13d0
ENG: "Even a river would be a bit much, wouldn't it?"

LABEL: 0x141a
ENG: In terms of other bodies of water...

LABEL: 0x151c
JPN: 「海や川以外の水場となると、ここかなって」
ENG: "Since rivers or the sea are out of the question, I thought that maybe this might be it."

LABEL: 0x15fa
JPN: 「ここを探すのはちょっと無理だな」
ENG: "You know, this doesn't actually make it any easier."

LABEL: 0x1636
JPN: ここの水を全部抜くぐらいしないと、探しようがない。
ENG: There wasn't much we could do in the way of searching. Unless we drained the whole dang thing, that is.

LABEL: 0x1678
JPN: それはそれで、面白そうだ。
ENG: Which in itself did sound pretty interesting.

LABEL: 0x172a
JPN: ため池を、気持ちよく泳ぎ回るというわけにもいかない。
ENG: We couldn't just take a leisurely swim through it, either.

LABEL: 0x176e
JPN: 仮にここに隠していたとしたら、お手上げとしか言いようが無い。
ENG: If it really was in here somewhere, then we'd have no way of getting at it.

LABEL: 0x1922
JPN: 身近すぎて、思いつかなかった。
ENG: I was so used to it, it never even occurred to me.

LABEL: 0x19e2
JPN: そろって、プールを眺める。
ENG: We stared into the water together.

LABEL: 0x1a0c
JPN: 太陽の光をうけて、プールの底がゆらゆらと揺れて見える。
ENG: The sunlight undulated at the bottom.

LABEL: 0x1a52
JPN: 「鍵がありそうには見えないな」

LABEL: 0x1a8a
JPN: 鍵を隠すようなくぼみも見当たらない。
ENG: I couldn't find anywhere one might hide something like that.

LABEL: 0x1ace
JPN: 「更衣室とかに隠してるのかな」
ENG: "Maybe it's in the changing rooms or something?"

LABEL: 0x1b02
JPN: 「うーん。それだと、海底ってことにはならないよな」
ENG: "Hmm, but then what do sea gods have to do with that?"

LABEL: 0x1bb2
ENG: "'Ocean gods'... What is that supposed to mean?"

LABEL: 0x1be6
JPN: 「プールにしろ、ため池にしろ、それらしきものはなかったよな」
ENG: "I sure don't see anything godlike around here. Not at the pond, either."

LABEL: 0x1c3c
JPN: 「かいじん……海神だとしたら、彫像でもたってるのか？」
ENG: "Should we be looking for some kind of statue, you think?"

LABEL: 0x1cbe
JPN: ただのかっこつけかもしれないけど、海神という言葉も無視できない。
ENG: It could've been embellished to sound edgy and cool, but we still couldn't ignore it outright.

LABEL: 0x1d0e
ENG: And then there's the other part...

LABEL: 0x1d62
JPN: 「かいじんって、別の意味なのかな」
ENG: "I wonder if 'ocean gods' is referring to something different."

LABEL: 0x1dd0
ENG: "I dunno, like, maybe it's the 'roooaaar' kind."

LABEL: 0x1e36
JPN: 「うけーっていって、きえーっていう」
ENG: "Y'know, those ones that're all like 'roooaaar'! Or like, 'graaawr'!"

LABEL: 0x1e9a
ENG: I put my imagination into overdrive.

LABEL: 0x1eb8
JPN: 「怪人のことか。戦隊ものにでてくる」
ENG: "Are you talking about like, a sea monster?"

LABEL: 0x1f88
JPN: 「ますます意味が分からなくなるな」
ENG: "That just makes things even more confusing."

LABEL: 0x2010
JPN: 同時に腹の音が鳴った。

LABEL: 0x2046
JPN: 時刻は、正午をまわろうとしていた。
ENG: It was just about past noon.

LABEL: 0x209a
JPN: そういえば、今日はうみちゃんが、残りもの片付けて下さいって言っていたな。
ENG: Speaking of which, Umi-chan asked me to help with leftovers today.

LABEL: 0x20f2
ENG: "I'm gonna head back to eat for now."

LABEL: 0x2158
ENG: "Oh, why don't you come along too?"

LABEL: 0x21c6
JPN: 「ううん。いいよ。私はいつも食堂で食べてるから」
ENG: "Nah, I'm all right. I always eat at the diner."

LABEL: 0x220c
JPN: 「そうか。じゃあ、１時間後にまた集合ということで」
ENG: "Oh, okay. Then we'll meet up in about an hour?"

LABEL: 0x2258
ENG: "Let's make sure we keep thinking until then."

LABEL: 0x23ac
JPN: 「すいません。辞書ってありますか」
ENG: "Sorry to bother you, but would you happen to have a dictionary lying around?"

LABEL: 0x26ee
JPN: 「食事をしながら辞書を読んでると、頭よさそうに見えるよな」
ENG: "Reading a dictionary while I eat makes me look pretty smart, wouldn'tcha say?"

LABEL: 0x2752
JPN: 「その発言が、すごく頭悪いですけど」
ENG: "Saying that out loud only makes you look stupid, just so you know."

LABEL: 0x278e
JPN: 「うみちゃんは、『かいてい』って聞いて、何を思い浮かべる？」
ENG: "Umi-chan, what do you think of when you hear the words 'companion way'?"

LABEL: 0x282e
ENG: "A path you walk with a friend?"

LABEL: 0x2892
ENG: "Why do you ask all of a sudden?"

LABEL: 0x2992
JPN: 辞書に、見たことのない言葉がのっている。
ENG: As I browsed the dictionary, I came across a word I had never seen before.

LABEL: 0x29ca
ENG: A 'companionway' was a... boat staircase of some kind?

LABEL: 0x2bb0
JPN: 「ちょうど食べ終わったところ」
ENG: "I was just about to finish up."

LABEL: 0x2c08
JPN: 「実は、ちょっと思いついたことがあるんだ」
ENG: "I came up with something while I was eating."

LABEL: 0x2c8e
JPN: 「私のほうでも、食べながら閃いたんだよ」
ENG: "What a coinkydink! I had a stroke of genius of my own!"

LABEL: 0x2d04
JPN: 「かいじんはうみがみ様のことでしょう」
ENG: "We're talking about a sea god, right?"

LABEL: 0x2d84
JPN: 「うん。うみがみっていうのはつまり」
ENG: "A god of the sea can only be..."

LABEL: 0x2dce
JPN: 「ウミガメのことじゃないかな」
ENG: "Sea turtles! Am I right or am I right?"

LABEL: 0x2e12
JPN: 「ウミガメとうみがみ。似てるよねぇ」
ENG: "They live hundreds of years, they even got 'sea' in the name. You feel me?"

LABEL: 0x2e5c
JPN: 「ウミガメといえばうらしま太郎だよね」
ENG: "And I dunno about you, but when I hear turtles, I think of the story of Urashima Tarou."

LABEL: 0x2ea8
JPN: 「ウミガメがその辺を歩いていて、海底まで案内してくれるんだよ」
ENG: "We just gotta make friends with one and he'll guide us to the treasure, along the companion way!"

LABEL: 0x2f0c
ENG: "That's gotta be it! It's just gotta!"

LABEL: 0x2fbc
JPN: 「俺も、食事をしながら考えてみたんだ」

LABEL: 0x3058
JPN: 「行ってみたいところがあるんだ。来てくれ」
ENG: "There's somewhere I want to try. Come with me."

LABEL: 0x313e
ENG: We made our way over to the town hall.

LABEL: 0x317a
ENG: "Is there something special about this place?"

LABEL: 0x31a4
JPN: 「神様がいるんじゃないかと」
ENG: "I thought we might find some gods here or something."

LABEL: 0x31ea
JPN: 「役場だからね。偉い人はいるかも」
ENG: "It is the town hall, I guess. Could be some bigwigs around."

LABEL: 0x3348
ENG: "I knew it. It all comes down to the big blue."

LABEL: 0x3370
JPN: 「海底って言ったらここしかないよな」
ENG: "It's gotta. The riddle's all about the ocean, after all."

LABEL: 0x33e6
JPN: 「もぐっても海底なんて調べようがないよな」
ENG: "Are we supposed to scan the ocean floor?"

LABEL: 0x343a
JPN: 「やっぱり亀を探すんじゃないかな」
ENG: "We better find us some turtle friends."

LABEL: 0x34cc
ENG: "U-Um, let's think this through a bit more."

LABEL: 0x35e2
JPN: 「海じゃないけど、水があって。底を調べることも出来るしね」
ENG: "It isn't the sea, but it does have water. And it's easier to search, that's for sure."

LABEL: 0x3632
JPN: 「でも見たところそれらしきものはないよな」
ENG: "I'm not seeing anything at a glance, though."

LABEL: 0x3676
JPN: それに、海神ってなんだろう。
ENG: And where did the ocean gods fit into it?

LABEL: 0x3716
ENG: "Nope! I was just gonna sploosh right in."

LABEL: 0x3744
JPN: 「それは……さすがにやめておけ」

LABEL: 0x378e
JPN: 「そうだね。先生に怒られちゃうね」
ENG: "Yeah, smart. We'd get in trouble with the teachers, wouldn't we?"

LABEL: 0x3932
ENG: "Companion way... A place you go to with friends..."

LABEL: 0x399a
JPN: 「なんでもない。別のところに行こう」

LABEL: 0x3ac8
JPN: 「この石段を登ったところにご神体を祭ったお堂があるらしい」
ENG: "See the temple at the top of these steps?"

LABEL: 0x3b4a
JPN: 「聞いた話では、海を守る神様が祭られているらしいけど」
ENG: "I heard it's dedicated to a god who protects the ocean."

LABEL: 0x3c36
ENG: "I-I don't think the turtles are related. Most likely."

LABEL: 0x3c78
JPN: 「かいじんは、海神様で。かいていはやっぱり、海の底ってこと？」
ENG: "So we have our ocean gods, now what about the 'companion way'? Is it walking down the path together?"

LABEL: 0x3d28
JPN: 隠せそうな場所があるとしたら……
ENG: If I were to hide something in a place like this...

LABEL: 0x3d58
JPN: 「石段の両脇に、灯籠がいくつか建っているだろう」
ENG: "You see all the lanterns following the steps on either side?"

LABEL: 0x3ea2
JPN: 「言っておくけどリーダーは私だよ？」
ENG: "For the record, I'm the leader. Got it?"

LABEL: 0x3fda
JPN: 探し始めてから２０分ほどして、鴎の歓声があがった。
ENG: About twenty minutes of searching later, Kamome shouted in glee.

LABEL: 0x405e
JPN: 「ほらこれ！　灯籠の裏側に隠してあった」
ENG: "Look, here! It was hidden behind this lamp!"

LABEL: 0x409c
JPN: 鴎が小さな布袋を俺に渡す。
ENG: Kamome handed me a little cloth bag.

LABEL: 0x40c6
JPN: 中には、確かに小さな固い感触があった。
ENG: Something cold and hard poked out at me from inside.

LABEL: 0x4120
ENG: "So this is one of those keys."

LABEL: 0x418e
ENG: "A companionway is a kind of staircase."

LABEL: 0x41c2
JPN: 「海神が守るかいてい。つまり、神社の石段ってことだ」
ENG: "'The companionway amongst the ocean gods.' In other words, the stairs to the shrine."

LABEL: 0x4250
ENG: "How was I supposed to know a word like that?"

LABEL: 0x42a2
JPN: 俺だって知らなかった。

LABEL: 0x439c
JPN: 「このヒントを書いたのは、よっぽどひねくれた子供だったんだろうな」
ENG: "The kid who wrote this must have been a crafty little bugger."

LABEL: 0x43f8
JPN: 「明らかに、海底にミスリードしようとしてたしな」
ENG: "Since he obviously tried to mislead us by separating the word into two."

LABEL: 0x4442
JPN: ほんとに海に潜って探そうとしたら、どうするんだ。
ENG: What if we had actually gone through with searching the ocean?

LABEL: 0x44be
JPN: 「でもとにかく、本当に鍵を隠していたんだな」
ENG: "But anyway, that confirms these things really are hidden around the island."

LABEL: 0x4504
JPN: 布の袋の中には、きれいにラッピングされた小さな鍵が入っていた。
ENG: There was a neatly wrapped key stowed inside the bag.

LABEL: 0x4552
JPN: 頭の部分には意匠が施されている。凝った作りの鍵だ。
ENG: An intricate design was carved into its head.

LABEL: 0x4730
JPN: なぜか当たり前のように、俺はスーツケースを押しながら、鴎を港まで送っていた。
ENG: For some reason, I found myself shuttling Kamome to the pier on her suitcase, as if it were the most natural thing in the world for me to do.

LABEL: 0x478c
ENG: Or maybe 'delivering' was a more apt word to use. What was I, a luggage valet?

LABEL: 0x481a
ENG: "I couldn't have done it without you!"

LABEL: 0x4870
JPN: 確かに鴎１人では無理だったな。

LABEL: 0x489e
JPN: 俺が分かったのも、偶然みたいなものだ。
ENG: To be fair, it was really pure chance that I'd figured it out.

LABEL: 0x48d4
JPN: 「まったく、もう少し単純なヒントにしてほしいな」
ENG: "Man, I wish they would've come up with simpler hints."

LABEL: 0x4944
JPN: 「今日はこの辺で解散するか」
ENG: "Should we go ahead and call it for today?"

LABEL: 0x49ca
JPN: 「明後日かもしれないけどな」
ENG: "Might be the next day. Who knows what I'll end up doing."

LABEL: 0x4a2a
JPN: 「明後日がだめなら明明後日があるさ」
ENG: "And if that's a no-go too, then there's always the day after."

LABEL: 0x4b06
JPN: 「羽依里、さてはテレビっ子じゃないな」
ENG: "No childhood memories in front of the ol' tube?"

LABEL: 0x4b42
JPN: 「まぁ、そんなに見なかったかなー」

LABEL: 0x4b7e
JPN: 同年代の友人がアニメの話をしていても、ついていけないことが多い。
ENG: I often couldn't keep up with the conversation around friends when anime came up.

LABEL: 0x4bce
JPN: 「一体子供の頃何して過ごしてたの」
ENG: "Then what in the heck DO ya have childhood memories of?"

LABEL: 0x4c2c
ENG: "Ooh, can't relate. You're my total opposite."

LABEL: 0x4c8a
JPN: 「この番組は、清楚なお嬢様と、ワイルドな野生児の提供でお送りします」
ENG: "This program is brought to you by a charming young lady and a wild, rugged wolf boy."

LABEL: 0x4ce4
JPN: 「誰が清楚なお嬢様で、誰がワイルドな野生児だ」
ENG: "And just where exactly is this charming young lady and this wild, rugged wolf boy you speak of?"

LABEL: 0x4d2c
JPN: 「とにかく。気が向いたらでいいから、また手伝ってね」
ENG: "Anyway, come lend me a hand again sometime. Just whenever ya feel like it."

LABEL: 0x4da0
ENG: "Whether it's tomorrow, or the day after tomorrow, or even the day after that."
